            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head/>
                <origin>Richmond Enquirer</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript>
                    <p>The Richmond "<emph rend="italic">Enquirer</emph>" advises Maryland and
                        Virginia promptly to interpose to prevent Mr. Lincoln's inauguration at
                        Washington, by taking possession of the Capitol without delay. It says such
                        a step will be unavoidable, sooner or later. In another article in the same
                        issue, it says: </p>
                    <p>If the Governor of Maryland, influenced by timidity or actuated by treachery,
                        shall longer delay to permit the people of that State to protect themselves,
                        can there not be found men bold and brave enough to unite with Virginians in
                        seizing the Capitol at Washington and the Federal defences within the two
                        States?</p>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Richmond Enquirer suggests that Maryland and Virginia seize the Distict of
                    Columbia to prevent Lincoln's inauguration.</summary>
                <note>aubrowser/ssjan61.html#1.1a</note>
                <look>x</look>
            </div>
